";}i:4;a:9:{s:5:"title";s:69:"EECI2010 Top Ten, #6! Solve Problems Quickly: An EE Guru Packed Event";s:4:"link";s:57:"http://expressionengine.com/blog/entry/eeci2010_topten_6/";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:14:"Leslie Camacho";}s:8:"category";s:15:"NewsThe Insider";s:8:"comments";s:57:"http://expressionengine.com/blog/entry/eeci2010_topten_6/";s:11:"description";s:1615:"<p><a href="http://expressionengine.com/blog/entry/eeci2010_top_ten/">Top Ten Reasons Why EECI is the Event of the Year</a>. <a href="http://eeci2010.com/">Register now</a>!</p>

<p>There is a good chance that at this very moment you are tackling a number of web development issues. There is also a good chance that at least a few of these are complex with no clear solution. That&#8217;s just a normal day in the life of a web professional. </p>

<p>No matter how comprehensive your web toolkit is clients will find a way to deliver a new challenge. You know that your skills plus EE and/or CI is up to the task and it will just be a matter of time before you amaze your client with a workable solution. But time is a precious thing, a commodity that always seems in short supply. </p>

<p>Now imagine a building packed with web professionals who bring with them an amazing array of skill sets and thousands and thousands of hours of collective experience. What if this building had an exclusive space with food, coffee, net access, work stations, all setup in way to encourage people to help each other solve complex issues quickly. </p>

<p>This place exists at EECI2010. It&#8217;s the CodeShare Corner hosted by <a href="http://solspace.com">Solspace</a>. </p>

<p>I saw it work firsthand at EECI2009 time and time again. The beautiful reality is that this isn&#8217;t limited to the CodeShare Corner, it will be unfolding everywhere, 24/7 for three days.</p>

<p>This is your building. This is your community. We take care of our own.</p>

<p>See you at <a href="http://eeci2010.com">EECI2010</a>.&nbsp; 
