</p>";}i:14;a:9:{s:5:"title";s:28:"SXSW UserVoice Events Chosen";s:4:"link";s:68:"http://expressionengine.com/blog/entry/sxsw_uservoice_events_chosen/";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:11:"Derek Jones";}s:8:"category";s:4:"News";s:8:"comments";s:68:"http://expressionengine.com/blog/entry/sxsw_uservoice_events_chosen/";s:11:"description";s:2321:"<p>Our UserVoice selected events for SXSW 2010 have been chosen.&nbsp; You, the community, have come up with some interesting topics, and we couldn&#8217;t be happier that we put this part of our SXSW agenda in your hands!&nbsp; Sign up now, as we will still be limiting these to small groups to maximize one on one interaction.</p>

<p><a href="http://expressionengine.com/forums/viewthread/146728/">Saturday, March 13, 10 - 11am Distributed development: how do you guys do it?!</a><br />
The primary topic will be that of working with a distributed team.&nbsp; EllisLab has team members in European countries, and all throughout North America.&nbsp; How do we work together?&nbsp; We’ll talk about technical, logistical, and human challenges of working tightly in this environment.&nbsp; If you have a distributed team and either need help or would like to help others from your experience, this is the group for you!</p>

<p><a href="http://expressionengine.com/forums/viewthread/146731/">Saturday, March 13, 4 - 5pm Module building from experts, the EllisLab team</a><br />
As described from UserVoice: &#8220;The EE team talks about extending EE 2 with a walk through of a module with a Q&amp;A from attendees.&#8221;&nbsp; We’ll go a step further and talk about ExpressionEngine 2.0’s new add-on types, on choosing what type of add-on to build a particular feature with, as well as the keys to successfully distributing and marketing an add-on to the ExpressionEngine community (both free and commercial).</p>

<p><a href="http://expressionengine.com/forums/viewthread/146732/">Sunday, March 14, 2 - 3pm CodeIgniter Web Apps with ExpressionEngine 2.0</a><br />
As suggested from UserVoice: &#8220;Before EE2.0 was released developers were getting very excited about EE2.0 being developed with CodeIgniter…Developers from both EE and CI camps were told of “dropping in” EE into a CodeIgniter build and harnessing the power of EE within a CI application. This discussion would be an overview of how CI works inside EE and how to extend it.&#8221;</p>

<p>At all three discussions, we&#8217;ll make sure that we have time for general discussion on various things you may wish to talk about that are not necessarily on topic for that group event.&nbsp; Thanks to everyone for the suggestions and votes!
